<br>
It makes sense for the Orb to become a focus item for the pets, we give up 6 focus items for it, I don't see why it shouldn't. Make it so it gives a bigger incease to the 57-60 pets, but a smaller one for the 61+, to leave room for improvement for PoP Focus Items (Which I highly doubt there are for our pets.)<br>
<br>
Epics should have never become obsolete. VI could of implemented quests throuought the expansions allowing you to increase its power (I.e. Stats, damage, whatever its right-clicky effect is.) So that maybe in a new expansion, droppable items are better than the epic, but once you complete the quests the epic is back at the top.<br>
<br>
But this would requrie extra work, and we know how much VI hates that. And even if they did it the quests probably wouldn't even work. *Cough cough* Sage quest *Cough cough*  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lordgojirax>LordGojirax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 421<br> <font color=#333333>(2/5/03 7:55:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=459.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojhead.jpg width=98 height=126></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /Sign</span><hr size=1> Yes, all epics should be retrofitted with at least SOME function that gives them some sort of continued reward, no matter how minor.<br>
