<br>
The mage epic quest as it stands today is very easy to get. I myself have a earth stave, and water stave in the bank. I have been epic for nearly a year now as well. One group of non-uber 60+ people can break hate, and kill every mini boss in hate. I know because my guild has done it. We got two staves in a week. Magi seems to always have it, and Hate at least on TT is not perma camped at all. It is normally empty for days.<br>
<br>
Now I know for the lvl 51 mage it might be hard to get because 6 lvl 51 toons can not break hate or kill the mini bosses. However it is suppose to be hard to get at lvl 51 because you do not need it at all at that level. The mage epic is the most overpowered epic from lvls 51-60 because it's power is static. The same thing that makes it extremely powerful pre-61 is the same thing that makes it extremely weak post 61. The power is static, and does not move. <br>
<br>
So yes the mage epic is very easy to get. My guild was able to get to 5th isle in less then 4 hours. We could have moved to isle 7 in 6 hours. Only reason it really takes so long is because the Keeper of Souls is on a 80min pop timer so no matter how fast you kill you still have to wait for him to pop. Other then that 80min bottle neck getting to isle 7 is cake.  PoA is no longer a 3 day trip, and with a 61+ enchanter they can mezz all of the bee splits on isle 6 with ease.<br>
<br>
So i am admitting that I to also finally believe that the mage epic quest is very easy to get even for those that are non-uber. If you do not have 6-10 friends at lvl 60 that you can convince to go to hate with you then i feel sorry for you hehe.<br>
<br>
Now with all that said.............I do believe the epic should be a focus item for the post 60 pets even though it is a kunark based item. Reason why is this.........<br>
<br>
The bard epic works as all instruments on ALL songs. I have a lvl 61 epic bard also.  I was a epic bard before i was a epic mage, and even with the post 60 songs the epic is still focusing those songs. That is a kunark weapon that is still having a dramatic affect on PoP content. The proc from the epic still is one of the best buffs in the game and still stacks with all buffs in the game.<br>
<br>
If the bard epic is allowed to work and giving singing bonus and instrument bonus to PoP songs then it is easy to conclude it wouldn't be out of place for the mage epic to focus post 60 pets. How can anyone argue against it when there is a clear example of a kunark epic that is still making PoP content easier.<br>
<br>
I still see lvl 65 rogues with epics even if in the offhand. I have two epic warriors in my guild both near 65, and both still using epic. Epic weapons are very hard to replace because the affects/stats are hard to replace. If you are in uber guild XX then yes it is easy to replace epics but if your guild is not uber they are hard to replace.<br>
<br>
So yes the epic is easy, yes it is 3 expansions old, and yes it is very easy to argue that it should focus post 60 pets. IMO the mage epic is one of the few that needs to be changed completely. It needs to be a focus item for all pets that increase hps by a certain percentage/dex and gives the elemental proc and damage shield to whatever pet you summon.  That would allow all pets to still be used instead of one and it would give the new pets the boost in power they need. I have the lvl 63 and 65 pet and i am hear to tell you that calling them a joke is way to nice. The earth pet is so crappy that I don't think there are words to really describe just how $hitty this pet is.............<br>
<br>
