However, I still think we have one of the most useful epics out there.  The epic pet *still* does a boatload of dmg given the proc it has, just is handicapped in that it's stun nuke doesn't hit the PoP mobs and the fact he can't tank as well.  I personally use the epic as a way to regain mana after a rez (usually summon one before the rez and summon/reclaim pet after).    <br>
<br>
If they did upgrade the Orb of Mastery, there would have to be some twinking of ALL the epics in general.  That would probably be a big class balancing nightmare.  Epics like the Beastlord, Ranger, Wizard, etc. don't really need to be tampered with because their effects are still some of the best out there.  The Warrior and Shadowknight epics are due for some sort of upgrade, because not many people even try for these (excepting just to say they did it or for the rather useful &quot;enraging blow&quot; effect on one of the warrior's swords).  If they did decide to upgrade the Orb of Mastery the focus idea sounds really good.  It would be the most balancing effect aside from raising the epic pet to level 60 (giving it enrage and useable stun nukes).  But still I would have to lean towards the sentiments that the magician epic still is very worthy of working towards. <br>
<br>
And about level 46 magicians with the epic--I was under the impression that ALL classes had to wait until 50 or 51 to even start their epic.  True it is a level 46 spell, but in order to utilize it at such a low level you'd have to deding down to 46.  Given the difficulty of the epic itself, one would be hard pressed to complete the epic (without lots of money or lots of friends) before level 55.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062">Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Arch Convoker of Solusek Ro and Grand Master Tinkerer (221)<br>
