<br>
About adding focus to all Epics....  Honestly, I don' think that is such a bad idea.  There are many reasons for this too.  Verant retrofitted many many old items with focus effects when that change was made in the game.  They did this because it was not a &quot;new&quot; balancing idea, they themselves realized spell focusing SHOULD have been done the whole time.  This was why the effects were added, people should not have worked so hard to get all that armor, then been forced to dump it all and get entirely new armor just because game designers finally woke up and realized it was broken.<br>
<br>
So, it's not really disputed that's what happened.  But when I look back on it, I see quests that took huge amounts of time and effort for many people.  If any items deserved to have focus effects added, then it would be epics.<br>
<br>
Now, about what focus's to add to all classes?  Well that's a tough question.  My first ideas would be to possibly have polls when logging in like they did for customer service questions.  Let the players pick for themselves what they want for their class.  OR maybe you could make a blanket change for all of them.  <br>
<br>
-Idea #1-<br>
Like perhaps part of the &quot;particle effect&quot; of having epic on was a bard type song that always played.  It should stack with all other spells/effects so the epic always has *some* use.  Non-melee casters could get 5% spell haste, and 5% mana saving.  Melee could get 10% haste.  Hybrids could get 2% spell haste, 2% mana saving, and 5% melee haste.<br>
<br>
-Idea #2-<br>
Let each class vote on their own.  They can pick from...<br>
Any of the level IV spell focus effects, Melee-haste X% in song form (so it stacks), or Y HP a tick regen.  If you argue that the spell focus should be max III effect, then I would argue the melee-related should cut in half (X/2 or Y/2) at 61. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Master Eandori Raintree<br>
60/61 Arch Mage<br>
